win11-window-tiling — Fedora KDE Plasma Edition
================================================

Windows 11-style window tiling for Fedora KDE Plasma Spin.

This edition installs the KZones KWin script for zone-based snapping and
configures Windows 11-style Super+Arrow keyboard shortcuts.

Requirements
------------

  Fedora KDE Plasma Spin with KWin (Plasma 6).

Install
-------

  sudo dnf install ./win11-window-tiling-1.0.0-1.fc41kde.noarch.rpm

Setup
-----

  win11-tiling-setup

Log out and back in after setup.

Usage
-----

  Super + Left/Right         Tile to left/right half
  Super + Up                 Maximize
  Super + Down               Minimize
  Super + Shift + Left       Top-left quarter
  Super + Shift + Right      Top-right quarter
  Super + Shift + Down       Bottom-left quarter
  Super + Shift + Up         Bottom-right quarter
  Drag to screen edges       Snap into KZones

Settings: System Settings > Window Management > KWin Scripts > KZones

Commands
--------

  win11-tiling-setup --status     Check install status
  win11-tiling-setup --uninstall  Remove KZones from your user profile
  win11-tile left                 Manually tile active window (CLI)

Build from source (on Fedora)
-----------------------------

  cd fedora-kde
  ./build.sh

